                            <comment id="16087540" author="jira-bot" created="Fri, 14 Jul 2017 16:20:33 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Commit 87a4b1765ffab2a965bbd2a5bfc2289c205d3592 in qpid-jms&apos;s branch refs/heads/master from &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=tabish121&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;tabish121&quot;&gt;tabish121&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
[ &lt;a href=&quot;https://git-wip-us.apache.org/repos/asf?p=qpid-jms.git;h=87a4b17&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://git-wip-us.apache.org/repos/asf?p=qpid-jms.git;h=87a4b17&lt;/a&gt; ]&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/QPIDJMS-299&quot; title=&quot;executor thread factories can retain closed connection objects due to implicit parent references&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;QPIDJMS-299&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;QPIDJMS-299&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; Don&apos;t create anonymous ThreadFactory instances&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Create a simple ThreadFactory object that can be used by&lt;br/&gt;
all the various places where we create executors instead&lt;br/&gt;
of using anonymous inner class which can carry and retain&lt;br/&gt;
references to the creator where no reference is needed.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;These dangle references can in some cases keep objects&lt;br/&gt;
alive longer than they should be or even indefinitely.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
